                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16950403-12-off42 t16950403-12-cd44"></join> last, as he was Riding home from London to his own house at Bromley in Kent; when he came very near his house he set was upon by Seven or eight men, who bound him, and afterwards laid him on the Ground, then they bound his Man who was with him, and made him go to the Door and Knock, as if his Master was with him; so the other Servant opening the Door they all rushed in, and bound all the Family, and then rifled the house, then came back to him, and led him into his house, left him bound; and then took three Horses out of the Stable and went away. This Prisoner <rs id="t16950403-12-verdict45" type="verdictDescription">
